         <abstract>
            <p>This paper deals with existence and characterization of best approximations to vector-valued functions. The approximations are themselves vector-valued functions with components taken from a linear space, but the constraint is imposed that certain of the approximation parameters should be identical for all components.</p>
          </abstract>
